      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;

    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');

}

  document.querySelectorAll('img.lazy').forEach(img => {
    img.loading = 'lazy';
    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now
    if (imgUrl.indexOf('/avatar/') > -1 && imgUrl.indexOf('?') === -1) {
      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

    img.classList.remove('lazy');

<a aria-hidden="true" href="#create-react-app" class="anchor" id="user-content-create-react-app"></a>Create React App <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://dev.azure.com/facebook/create-react-app/_build/latest?definitionId=1&branchName=main" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" alt="Build Status" src="https://dev.azure.com/facebook/create-react-app/_apis/build/status/facebook.create-react-app?branchName=main" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a> <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" alt="PRs Welcome" src="https://img.shields.io/badge/PRs-welcome-green.svg" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a>
</h1>
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://create-react-app.dev/img/logo.svg" class="no-attachment-icon" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" width="20%" src="https://create-react-app.dev/img/logo.svg" align="right" alt="Logo" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="5:1-5:46">Create React apps with no build configuration.</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="7:1-9:0">
<li data-sourcepos="7:1-7:66">
<a href="#creating-an-app">Creating an App</a> – How to create a new app.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="8:1-9:0">
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/" target="_blank">User Guide</a> – How to develop apps bootstrapped with Create React App.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="10:1-12:129">Create React App works on macOS, Windows, and Linux.<br>
If something doesn’t work, please <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/issues/new" target="_blank">file an issue</a>.<br>
If you have questions or need help, please ask in <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/discussions" target="_blank">GitHub Discussions</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="14:1-14:17">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#quick-overview" class="anchor" id="user-content-quick-overview"></a>Quick Overview</h2>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="16:1-20:3" id="code-3"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1">npx create-react-app my-app</span>
<span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC2"><span class="nb">cd </span>my-app</span>
<span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC3">npm start</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-3"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="22:1-22:270">If you've previously installed <code>create-react-app</code> globally via <code>npm install -g create-react-app</code>, we recommend you uninstall the package using <code>npm uninstall -g create-react-app</code> or <code>yarn global remove create-react-app</code> to ensure that npx always uses the latest version.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="24:1-24:231"><em>(<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://medium.com/@maybekatz/introducing-npx-an-npm-package-runner-55f7d4bd282b" target="_blank">npx</a> comes with npm 5.2+ and higher, see <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://gist.github.com/gaearon/4064d3c23a77c74a3614c498a8bb1c5f" target="_blank">instructions for older npm versions</a>)</em></p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="26:1-27:91">Then open <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="http://localhost:3000/" target="_blank">http://localhost:3000/</a> to see your app.<br>
When you’re ready to deploy to production, create a minified bundle with <code>npm run build</code>.</p>
<p dir="auto" align="center">
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/facebook/create-react-app@27b42ac7efa018f2541153ab30d63180f5fa39e0/screencast.svg" class="no-attachment-icon" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" alt="npm start" width="600" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/facebook/create-react-app@27b42ac7efa018f2541153ab30d63180f5fa39e0/screencast.svg" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a>
</p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="33:1-33:27">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#get-started-immediately" class="anchor" id="user-content-get-started-immediately"></a>Get Started Immediately</h3>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="35:1-36:68">You <strong>don’t</strong> need to install or configure tools like webpack or Babel.<br>
They are preconfigured and hidden so that you can focus on the code.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="38:1-38:42">Create a project, and you’re good to go.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="40:1-40:18">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#creating-an-app" class="anchor" id="user-content-creating-an-app"></a>Creating an App</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="42:1-42:402"><strong>You’ll need to have Node 14.0.0 or later version on your local development machine</strong> (but it’s not required on the server). We recommend using the latest LTS version. You can use <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/creationix/nvm#installation" target="_blank">nvm</a> (macOS/Linux) or <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/coreybutler/nvm-windows#node-version-manager-nvm-for-windows" target="_blank">nvm-windows</a> to switch Node versions between different projects.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="44:1-44:65">To create a new app, you may choose one of the following methods:</p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="46:1-46:7">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npx" class="anchor" id="user-content-npx"></a>npx</h3>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="48:1-50:3" id="code-4"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1">npx create-react-app my-app</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-4"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="52:1-52:261"><em>(<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://medium.com/@maybekatz/introducing-npx-an-npm-package-runner-55f7d4bd282b" target="_blank">npx</a> is a package runner tool that comes with npm 5.2+ and higher, see <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://gist.github.com/gaearon/4064d3c23a77c74a3614c498a8bb1c5f" target="_blank">instructions for older npm versions</a>)</em></p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="54:1-54:7">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npm" class="anchor" id="user-content-npm"></a>npm</h3>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="56:1-58:3" id="code-5"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1">npm init react-app my-app</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-5"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="60:1-60:49"><em><code>npm init <initializer></code> is available in npm 6+</em></p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="62:1-62:8">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#yarn" class="anchor" id="user-content-yarn"></a>Yarn</h3>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="64:1-66:3" id="code-6"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1">yarn create react-app my-app</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-6"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="68:1-68:112"><em><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://yarnpkg.com/lang/en/docs/cli/create/" target="_blank"><code>yarn create <starter-kit-package></code></a> is available in Yarn 0.25+</em></p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="70:1-71:110">It will create a directory called <code>my-app</code> inside the current folder.<br>
Inside that directory, it will generate the initial project structure and install the transitive dependencies:</p>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-plaintext white" lang="plaintext" data-sourcepos="73:1-92:3" id="code-7"><code><span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC1">my-app</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC2">├── README.md</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC3">├── node_modules</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC4">├── package.json</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC5">├── .gitignore</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC6">├── public</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC7">│   ├── favicon.ico</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC8">│   ├── index.html</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC9">│   └── manifest.json</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC10">└── src</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC11">    ├── App.css</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC12">    ├── App.js</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC13">    ├── App.test.js</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC14">    ├── index.css</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC15">    ├── index.js</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC16">    ├── logo.svg</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC17">    └── serviceWorker.js</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC18">    └── setupTests.js</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-7"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="94:1-95:64">No configuration or complicated folder structures, only the files you need to build your app.<br>
Once the installation is done, you can open your project folder:</p>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="97:1-99:3" id="code-8"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1"><span class="nb">cd </span>my-app</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-8"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="101:1-101:69">Inside the newly created project, you can run some built-in commands:</p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="103:1-103:31">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npm-start-or-yarn-start" class="anchor" id="user-content-npm-start-or-yarn-start"></a><code>npm start</code> or <code>yarn start</code>
</h3>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="105:1-106:78">Runs the app in development mode.<br>
Open <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="http://localhost:3000" target="_blank">http://localhost:3000</a> to view it in the browser.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="108:1-109:63">The page will automatically reload if you make changes to the code.<br>
You will see the build errors and lint warnings in the console.</p>
<p dir="auto" align="center">
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/marionebl/create-react-app@9f6282671c54f0874afd37a72f6689727b562498/screencast-error.svg" class="no-attachment-icon" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" alt="Build errors" width="600" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/marionebl/create-react-app@9f6282671c54f0874afd37a72f6689727b562498/screencast-error.svg" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a>
</p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="115:1-115:29">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npm-test-or-yarn-test" class="anchor" id="user-content-npm-test-or-yarn-test"></a><code>npm test</code> or <code>yarn test</code>
</h3>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="117:1-118:70">Runs the test watcher in an interactive mode.<br>
By default, runs tests related to files changed since the last commit.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="120:1-120:90"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/running-tests" target="_blank">Read more about testing.</a></p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="122:1-122:35">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npm-run-build-or-yarn-build" class="anchor" id="user-content-npm-run-build-or-yarn-build"></a><code>npm run build</code> or <code>yarn build</code>
</h3>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="124:1-125:95">Builds the app for production to the <code>build</code> folder.<br>
It correctly bundles React in production mode and optimizes the build for the best performance.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="127:1-127:63">The build is minified and the filenames include the hashes.<br></p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="129:1-129:33">Your app is ready to be deployed.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="131:1-131:13">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#user-guide" class="anchor" id="user-content-user-guide"></a>User Guide</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="133:1-133:144">You can find detailed instructions on using Create React App and many tips in <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/" target="_blank">its documentation</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="135:1-135:33">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#how-to-update-to-new-versions" class="anchor" id="user-content-how-to-update-to-new-versions"></a>How to Update to New Versions?</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="137:1-137:139">Please refer to the <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/updating-to-new-releases" target="_blank">User Guide</a> for this and other information.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="139:1-139:13">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#philosophy" class="anchor" id="user-content-philosophy"></a>Philosophy</h2>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="141:1-146:0">
<li data-sourcepos="141:1-142:0">
<p data-sourcepos="141:3-141:176"><strong>One Dependency:</strong> There is only one build dependency. It uses webpack, Babel, ESLint, and other amazing projects, but provides a cohesive curated experience on top of them.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="143:1-144:0">
<p data-sourcepos="143:3-143:197"><strong>No Configuration Required:</strong> You don't need to configure anything. A reasonably good configuration of both development and production builds is handled for you so you can focus on writing code.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="145:1-146:0">
<p data-sourcepos="145:3-145:226"><strong>No Lock-In:</strong> You can “eject” to a custom setup at any time. Run a single command, and all the configuration and build dependencies will be moved directly into your project, so you can pick up right where you left off.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="147:1-147:21">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#whats-included" class="anchor" id="user-content-whats-included"></a>What’s Included?</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="149:1-149:87">Your environment will have everything you need to build a modern single-page React app:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="151:1-159:0">
<li data-sourcepos="151:1-151:54">React, JSX, ES6, TypeScript and Flow syntax support.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="152:1-152:61">Language extras beyond ES6 like the object spread operator.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="153:1-153:69">Autoprefixed CSS, so you don’t need <code>-webkit-</code> or other prefixes.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="154:1-154:83">A fast interactive unit test runner with built-in support for coverage reporting.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="155:1-155:61">A live development server that warns about common mistakes.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="156:1-156:90">A build script to bundle JS, CSS, and images for production, with hashes and sourcemaps.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="157:1-157:444">An offline-first <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/getting-started/primers/service-workers" target="_blank">service worker</a> and a <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/engage-and-retain/web-app-manifest/" target="_blank">web app manifest</a>, meeting all the <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/making-a-progressive-web-app" target="_blank">Progressive Web App</a> criteria. (<em>Note: Using the service worker is opt-in as of <code>react-scripts@2.0.0</code> and higher</em>)</li>
<li data-sourcepos="158:1-159:0">Hassle-free updates for the above tools with a single dependency.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="160:1-160:119">Check out <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/nitishdayal/cra_closer_look" target="_blank">this guide</a> for an overview of how these tools fit together.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="162:1-162:296">The tradeoff is that <strong>these tools are preconfigured to work in a specific way</strong>. If your project needs more customization, you can <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/available-scripts#npm-run-eject" target="_blank">"eject"</a> and customize it, but then you will need to maintain this configuration.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="164:1-164:23">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#popular-alternatives" class="anchor" id="user-content-popular-alternatives"></a>Popular Alternatives</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="166:1-166:36">Create React App is a great fit for:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="168:1-171:0">
<li data-sourcepos="168:1-168:79">
<strong>Learning React</strong> in a comfortable and feature-rich development environment.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="169:1-169:50"><strong>Starting new single-page React applications.</strong></li>
<li data-sourcepos="170:1-171:0">
<strong>Creating examples</strong> with React for your libraries and components.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="172:1-172:71">Here are a few common cases where you might want to try something else:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="174:1-185:0">
<li data-sourcepos="174:1-175:0">
<p data-sourcepos="174:3-174:209">If you want to <strong>try React</strong> without hundreds of transitive build tool dependencies, consider <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://reactjs.org/docs/getting-started.html#try-react" target="_blank">using a single HTML file or an online sandbox instead</a>.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="176:1-177:0">
<p data-sourcepos="176:3-176:476">If you need to <strong>integrate React code with a server-side template framework</strong> like Rails, Django or Symfony, or if you’re <strong>not building a single-page app</strong>, consider using <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/insin/nwb" target="_blank">nwb</a>, or <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://neutrino.js.org/" target="_blank">Neutrino</a> which are more flexible. For Rails specifically, you can use <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/rails/webpacker" target="_blank">Rails Webpacker</a>. For Symfony, try <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://symfony.com/doc/current/frontend/encore/reactjs.html" target="_blank">Symfony's webpack Encore</a>.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="178:1-179:0">
<p data-sourcepos="178:3-178:265">If you need to <strong>publish a React component</strong>, <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/insin/nwb" target="_blank">nwb</a> can <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/insin/nwb#react-components-and-libraries" target="_blank">also do this</a>, as well as <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://neutrino.js.org/packages/react-components/" target="_blank">Neutrino's react-components preset</a>.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="180:1-181:0">
<p data-sourcepos="180:3-180:248">If you want to do <strong>server rendering</strong> with React and Node.js, check out <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://nextjs.org/" target="_blank">Next.js</a> or <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/jaredpalmer/razzle" target="_blank">Razzle</a>. Create React App is agnostic of the backend, and only produces static HTML/JS/CSS bundles.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="182:1-183:0">
<p data-sourcepos="182:3-182:301">If your website is <strong>mostly static</strong> (for example, a portfolio or a blog), consider using <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.gatsbyjs.org/" target="_blank">Gatsby</a> or <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://nextjs.org/" target="_blank">Next.js</a>. Unlike Create React App, Gatsby pre-renders the website into HTML at build time. Next.js supports both server rendering and pre-rendering.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="184:1-185:0">
<p data-sourcepos="184:3-184:158">Finally, if you need <strong>more customization</strong>, check out <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://neutrino.js.org/" target="_blank">Neutrino</a> and its <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://neutrino.js.org/packages/react/" target="_blank">React preset</a>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="186:1-186:64">All of the above tools can work with little to no configuration.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="188:1-188:120">If you prefer configuring the build yourself, <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://reactjs.org/docs/add-react-to-a-website.html" target="_blank">follow this guide</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="190:1-190:15">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#react-native" class="anchor" id="user-content-react-native"></a>React Native</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="192:1-193:55">Looking for something similar, but for React Native?<br>
Check out <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/expo/expo-cli" target="_blank">Expo CLI</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="195:1-195:15">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#contributing" class="anchor" id="user-content-contributing"></a>Contributing</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="197:1-197:168">We'd love to have your helping hand on <code>create-react-app</code>! See <a class="gfm" href="/byteblaze/create-react-app/-/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a> for more information on what we're looking for and how to get started.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="199:1-199:30">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#supporting-create-react-app" class="anchor" id="user-content-supporting-create-react-app"></a>Supporting Create React App</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="201:1-201:256">Create React App is a community maintained project and all contributors are volunteers. If you'd like to support the future development of Create React App then please consider donating to our <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://opencollective.com/create-react-app" target="_blank">Open Collective</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="203:1-203:10">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#credits" class="anchor" id="user-content-credits"></a>Credits</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="205:1-206:176">This project exists thanks to all the people who <a class="gfm" href="/byteblaze/create-react-app/-/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">contribute</a>.<br>
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/graphs/contributors" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" src="https://opencollective.com/create-react-app/contributors.svg?width=890&button=false" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a></p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="208:1-208:76">Thanks to <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.netlify.com/" target="_blank">Netlify</a> for hosting our documentation.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="210:1-210:19">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#acknowledgements" class="anchor" id="user-content-acknowledgements"></a>Acknowledgements</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="212:1-212:94">We are grateful to the authors of existing related projects for their ideas and collaboration:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="214:1-217:0">
<li data-sourcepos="214:1-214:46"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/eanplatter" target="_blank">@eanplatter</a></li>
<li data-sourcepos="215:1-215:36"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/insin" target="_blank">@insin</a></li>
<li data-sourcepos="216:1-217:0"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/mxstbr" target="_blank">@mxstbr</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="218:1-218:10">

<div class="file-content md">
<h1 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="1:1-1:381">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#create-react-app" class="anchor" id="user-content-create-react-app"></a>Create React App <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://dev.azure.com/facebook/create-react-app/_build/latest?definitionId=1&branchName=main" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" alt="Build Status" src="https://dev.azure.com/facebook/create-react-app/_apis/build/status/facebook.create-react-app?branchName=main" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a> <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" alt="PRs Welcome" src="https://img.shields.io/badge/PRs-welcome-green.svg" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a>
</h1>
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://create-react-app.dev/img/logo.svg" class="no-attachment-icon" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" width="20%" src="https://create-react-app.dev/img/logo.svg" align="right" alt="Logo" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="5:1-5:46">Create React apps with no build configuration.</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="7:1-9:0">
<li data-sourcepos="7:1-7:66">
<a href="#creating-an-app">Creating an App</a> – How to create a new app.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="8:1-9:0">
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/" target="_blank">User Guide</a> – How to develop apps bootstrapped with Create React App.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="10:1-12:129">Create React App works on macOS, Windows, and Linux.<br>
If something doesn’t work, please <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/issues/new" target="_blank">file an issue</a>.<br>
If you have questions or need help, please ask in <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/discussions" target="_blank">GitHub Discussions</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="14:1-14:17">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#quick-overview" class="anchor" id="user-content-quick-overview"></a>Quick Overview</h2>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="16:1-20:3" id="code-3"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1">npx create-react-app my-app</span>
<span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC2"><span class="nb">cd </span>my-app</span>
<span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC3">npm start</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-3"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="22:1-22:270">If you've previously installed <code>create-react-app</code> globally via <code>npm install -g create-react-app</code>, we recommend you uninstall the package using <code>npm uninstall -g create-react-app</code> or <code>yarn global remove create-react-app</code> to ensure that npx always uses the latest version.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="24:1-24:231"><em>(<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://medium.com/@maybekatz/introducing-npx-an-npm-package-runner-55f7d4bd282b" target="_blank">npx</a> comes with npm 5.2+ and higher, see <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://gist.github.com/gaearon/4064d3c23a77c74a3614c498a8bb1c5f" target="_blank">instructions for older npm versions</a>)</em></p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="26:1-27:91">Then open <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="http://localhost:3000/" target="_blank">http://localhost:3000/</a> to see your app.<br>
When you’re ready to deploy to production, create a minified bundle with <code>npm run build</code>.</p>
<p dir="auto" align="center">
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/facebook/create-react-app@27b42ac7efa018f2541153ab30d63180f5fa39e0/screencast.svg" class="no-attachment-icon" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" alt="npm start" width="600" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/facebook/create-react-app@27b42ac7efa018f2541153ab30d63180f5fa39e0/screencast.svg" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a>
</p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="33:1-33:27">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#get-started-immediately" class="anchor" id="user-content-get-started-immediately"></a>Get Started Immediately</h3>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="35:1-36:68">You <strong>don’t</strong> need to install or configure tools like webpack or Babel.<br>
They are preconfigured and hidden so that you can focus on the code.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="38:1-38:42">Create a project, and you’re good to go.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="40:1-40:18">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#creating-an-app" class="anchor" id="user-content-creating-an-app"></a>Creating an App</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="42:1-42:402"><strong>You’ll need to have Node 14.0.0 or later version on your local development machine</strong> (but it’s not required on the server). We recommend using the latest LTS version. You can use <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/creationix/nvm#installation" target="_blank">nvm</a> (macOS/Linux) or <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/coreybutler/nvm-windows#node-version-manager-nvm-for-windows" target="_blank">nvm-windows</a> to switch Node versions between different projects.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="44:1-44:65">To create a new app, you may choose one of the following methods:</p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="46:1-46:7">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npx" class="anchor" id="user-content-npx"></a>npx</h3>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="48:1-50:3" id="code-4"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1">npx create-react-app my-app</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-4"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="52:1-52:261"><em>(<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://medium.com/@maybekatz/introducing-npx-an-npm-package-runner-55f7d4bd282b" target="_blank">npx</a> is a package runner tool that comes with npm 5.2+ and higher, see <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://gist.github.com/gaearon/4064d3c23a77c74a3614c498a8bb1c5f" target="_blank">instructions for older npm versions</a>)</em></p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="54:1-54:7">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npm" class="anchor" id="user-content-npm"></a>npm</h3>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="56:1-58:3" id="code-5"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1">npm init react-app my-app</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-5"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="60:1-60:49"><em><code>npm init <initializer></code> is available in npm 6+</em></p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="62:1-62:8">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#yarn" class="anchor" id="user-content-yarn"></a>Yarn</h3>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="64:1-66:3" id="code-6"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1">yarn create react-app my-app</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-6"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="68:1-68:112"><em><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://yarnpkg.com/lang/en/docs/cli/create/" target="_blank"><code>yarn create <starter-kit-package></code></a> is available in Yarn 0.25+</em></p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="70:1-71:110">It will create a directory called <code>my-app</code> inside the current folder.<br>
Inside that directory, it will generate the initial project structure and install the transitive dependencies:</p>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-plaintext white" lang="plaintext" data-sourcepos="73:1-92:3" id="code-7"><code><span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC1">my-app</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC2">├── README.md</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC3">├── node_modules</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC4">├── package.json</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC5">├── .gitignore</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC6">├── public</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC7">│   ├── favicon.ico</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC8">│   ├── index.html</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC9">│   └── manifest.json</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC10">└── src</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC11">    ├── App.css</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC12">    ├── App.js</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC13">    ├── App.test.js</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC14">    ├── index.css</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC15">    ├── index.js</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC16">    ├── logo.svg</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC17">    └── serviceWorker.js</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC18">    └── setupTests.js</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-7"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="94:1-95:64">No configuration or complicated folder structures, only the files you need to build your app.<br>
Once the installation is done, you can open your project folder:</p>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="sh" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-shell white" lang="shell" data-sourcepos="97:1-99:3" id="code-8"><code><span lang="shell" class="line" id="LC1"><span class="nb">cd </span>my-app</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-8"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="101:1-101:69">Inside the newly created project, you can run some built-in commands:</p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="103:1-103:31">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npm-start-or-yarn-start" class="anchor" id="user-content-npm-start-or-yarn-start"></a><code>npm start</code> or <code>yarn start</code>
</h3>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="105:1-106:78">Runs the app in development mode.<br>
Open <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="http://localhost:3000" target="_blank">http://localhost:3000</a> to view it in the browser.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="108:1-109:63">The page will automatically reload if you make changes to the code.<br>
You will see the build errors and lint warnings in the console.</p>
<p dir="auto" align="center">
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/marionebl/create-react-app@9f6282671c54f0874afd37a72f6689727b562498/screencast-error.svg" class="no-attachment-icon" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" alt="Build errors" width="600" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/marionebl/create-react-app@9f6282671c54f0874afd37a72f6689727b562498/screencast-error.svg" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a>
</p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="115:1-115:29">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npm-test-or-yarn-test" class="anchor" id="user-content-npm-test-or-yarn-test"></a><code>npm test</code> or <code>yarn test</code>
</h3>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="117:1-118:70">Runs the test watcher in an interactive mode.<br>
By default, runs tests related to files changed since the last commit.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="120:1-120:90"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/running-tests" target="_blank">Read more about testing.</a></p>
<h3 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="122:1-122:35">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#npm-run-build-or-yarn-build" class="anchor" id="user-content-npm-run-build-or-yarn-build"></a><code>npm run build</code> or <code>yarn build</code>
</h3>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="124:1-125:95">Builds the app for production to the <code>build</code> folder.<br>
It correctly bundles React in production mode and optimizes the build for the best performance.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="127:1-127:63">The build is minified and the filenames include the hashes.<br></p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="129:1-129:33">Your app is ready to be deployed.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="131:1-131:13">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#user-guide" class="anchor" id="user-content-user-guide"></a>User Guide</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="133:1-133:144">You can find detailed instructions on using Create React App and many tips in <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/" target="_blank">its documentation</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="135:1-135:33">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#how-to-update-to-new-versions" class="anchor" id="user-content-how-to-update-to-new-versions"></a>How to Update to New Versions?</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="137:1-137:139">Please refer to the <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/updating-to-new-releases" target="_blank">User Guide</a> for this and other information.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="139:1-139:13">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#philosophy" class="anchor" id="user-content-philosophy"></a>Philosophy</h2>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="141:1-146:0">
<li data-sourcepos="141:1-142:0">
<p data-sourcepos="141:3-141:176"><strong>One Dependency:</strong> There is only one build dependency. It uses webpack, Babel, ESLint, and other amazing projects, but provides a cohesive curated experience on top of them.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="143:1-144:0">
<p data-sourcepos="143:3-143:197"><strong>No Configuration Required:</strong> You don't need to configure anything. A reasonably good configuration of both development and production builds is handled for you so you can focus on writing code.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="145:1-146:0">
<p data-sourcepos="145:3-145:226"><strong>No Lock-In:</strong> You can “eject” to a custom setup at any time. Run a single command, and all the configuration and build dependencies will be moved directly into your project, so you can pick up right where you left off.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="147:1-147:21">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#whats-included" class="anchor" id="user-content-whats-included"></a>What’s Included?</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="149:1-149:87">Your environment will have everything you need to build a modern single-page React app:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="151:1-159:0">
<li data-sourcepos="151:1-151:54">React, JSX, ES6, TypeScript and Flow syntax support.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="152:1-152:61">Language extras beyond ES6 like the object spread operator.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="153:1-153:69">Autoprefixed CSS, so you don’t need <code>-webkit-</code> or other prefixes.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="154:1-154:83">A fast interactive unit test runner with built-in support for coverage reporting.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="155:1-155:61">A live development server that warns about common mistakes.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="156:1-156:90">A build script to bundle JS, CSS, and images for production, with hashes and sourcemaps.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="157:1-157:444">An offline-first <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/getting-started/primers/service-workers" target="_blank">service worker</a> and a <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/engage-and-retain/web-app-manifest/" target="_blank">web app manifest</a>, meeting all the <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/making-a-progressive-web-app" target="_blank">Progressive Web App</a> criteria. (<em>Note: Using the service worker is opt-in as of <code>react-scripts@2.0.0</code> and higher</em>)</li>
<li data-sourcepos="158:1-159:0">Hassle-free updates for the above tools with a single dependency.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="160:1-160:119">Check out <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/nitishdayal/cra_closer_look" target="_blank">this guide</a> for an overview of how these tools fit together.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="162:1-162:296">The tradeoff is that <strong>these tools are preconfigured to work in a specific way</strong>. If your project needs more customization, you can <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/available-scripts#npm-run-eject" target="_blank">"eject"</a> and customize it, but then you will need to maintain this configuration.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="164:1-164:23">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#popular-alternatives" class="anchor" id="user-content-popular-alternatives"></a>Popular Alternatives</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="166:1-166:36">Create React App is a great fit for:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="168:1-171:0">
<li data-sourcepos="168:1-168:79">
<strong>Learning React</strong> in a comfortable and feature-rich development environment.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="169:1-169:50"><strong>Starting new single-page React applications.</strong></li>
<li data-sourcepos="170:1-171:0">
<strong>Creating examples</strong> with React for your libraries and components.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="172:1-172:71">Here are a few common cases where you might want to try something else:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="174:1-185:0">
<li data-sourcepos="174:1-175:0">
<p data-sourcepos="174:3-174:209">If you want to <strong>try React</strong> without hundreds of transitive build tool dependencies, consider <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://reactjs.org/docs/getting-started.html#try-react" target="_blank">using a single HTML file or an online sandbox instead</a>.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="176:1-177:0">
<p data-sourcepos="176:3-176:476">If you need to <strong>integrate React code with a server-side template framework</strong> like Rails, Django or Symfony, or if you’re <strong>not building a single-page app</strong>, consider using <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/insin/nwb" target="_blank">nwb</a>, or <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://neutrino.js.org/" target="_blank">Neutrino</a> which are more flexible. For Rails specifically, you can use <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/rails/webpacker" target="_blank">Rails Webpacker</a>. For Symfony, try <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://symfony.com/doc/current/frontend/encore/reactjs.html" target="_blank">Symfony's webpack Encore</a>.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="178:1-179:0">
<p data-sourcepos="178:3-178:265">If you need to <strong>publish a React component</strong>, <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/insin/nwb" target="_blank">nwb</a> can <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/insin/nwb#react-components-and-libraries" target="_blank">also do this</a>, as well as <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://neutrino.js.org/packages/react-components/" target="_blank">Neutrino's react-components preset</a>.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="180:1-181:0">
<p data-sourcepos="180:3-180:248">If you want to do <strong>server rendering</strong> with React and Node.js, check out <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://nextjs.org/" target="_blank">Next.js</a> or <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/jaredpalmer/razzle" target="_blank">Razzle</a>. Create React App is agnostic of the backend, and only produces static HTML/JS/CSS bundles.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="182:1-183:0">
<p data-sourcepos="182:3-182:301">If your website is <strong>mostly static</strong> (for example, a portfolio or a blog), consider using <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.gatsbyjs.org/" target="_blank">Gatsby</a> or <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://nextjs.org/" target="_blank">Next.js</a>. Unlike Create React App, Gatsby pre-renders the website into HTML at build time. Next.js supports both server rendering and pre-rendering.</p>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="184:1-185:0">
<p data-sourcepos="184:3-184:158">Finally, if you need <strong>more customization</strong>, check out <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://neutrino.js.org/" target="_blank">Neutrino</a> and its <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://neutrino.js.org/packages/react/" target="_blank">React preset</a>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="186:1-186:64">All of the above tools can work with little to no configuration.</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="188:1-188:120">If you prefer configuring the build yourself, <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://reactjs.org/docs/add-react-to-a-website.html" target="_blank">follow this guide</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="190:1-190:15">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#react-native" class="anchor" id="user-content-react-native"></a>React Native</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="192:1-193:55">Looking for something similar, but for React Native?<br>
Check out <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/expo/expo-cli" target="_blank">Expo CLI</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="195:1-195:15">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#contributing" class="anchor" id="user-content-contributing"></a>Contributing</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="197:1-197:168">We'd love to have your helping hand on <code>create-react-app</code>! See <a class="gfm" href="/byteblaze/create-react-app/-/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a> for more information on what we're looking for and how to get started.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="199:1-199:30">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#supporting-create-react-app" class="anchor" id="user-content-supporting-create-react-app"></a>Supporting Create React App</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="201:1-201:256">Create React App is a community maintained project and all contributors are volunteers. If you'd like to support the future development of Create React App then please consider donating to our <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://opencollective.com/create-react-app" target="_blank">Open Collective</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="203:1-203:10">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#credits" class="anchor" id="user-content-credits"></a>Credits</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="205:1-206:176">This project exists thanks to all the people who <a class="gfm" href="/byteblaze/create-react-app/-/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">contribute</a>.<br>
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/graphs/contributors" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" src="https://opencollective.com/create-react-app/contributors.svg?width=890&button=false" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a></p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="208:1-208:76">Thanks to <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.netlify.com/" target="_blank">Netlify</a> for hosting our documentation.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="210:1-210:19">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#acknowledgements" class="anchor" id="user-content-acknowledgements"></a>Acknowledgements</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="212:1-212:94">We are grateful to the authors of existing related projects for their ideas and collaboration:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="214:1-217:0">
<li data-sourcepos="214:1-214:46"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/eanplatter" target="_blank">@eanplatter</a></li>
<li data-sourcepos="215:1-215:36"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/insin" target="_blank">@insin</a></li>
<li data-sourcepos="216:1-217:0"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/mxstbr" target="_blank">@mxstbr</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="218:1-218:10">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#license" class="anchor" id="user-content-license"></a>License</h2>

    img.classList.remove('lazy');

  document.querySelectorAll('img.lazy').forEach(img => {
    img.loading = 'lazy';
    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now
    if (imgUrl.indexOf('/avatar/') > -1 && imgUrl.indexOf('?') === -1) {
      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

if ('loading' in HTMLImageElement.prototype) {
  document.querySelectorAll('img.lazy').forEach(img => {
    img.loading = 'lazy';
    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now
    if (imgUrl.indexOf('/avatar/') > -1 && imgUrl.indexOf('?') === -1) {
      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

//]]>
</script>

<div class="file-content md">
<p dir="auto" align="center">
  <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://buck.build/static/og.png" class="no-attachment-icon" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" width="20%" alt="logo" src="https://buck.build/static/og.png" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a>
</p>
<h1 dir="auto" align="center">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#buck" class="anchor" id="user-content-buck"></a>
  Buck
</h1>
<p dir="auto" align="center">
  Buck is a build tool. To see what Buck can do for you, check out the documentation at <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="http://buck.build/" target="_blank">http://buck.build/</a>.
</p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="11:1-11:109"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://circleci.com/gh/facebook/buck" target="_blank"><img class="js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" alt="Build Status" src="https://circleci.com/gh/facebook/buck.svg?style=svg" loading="lazy" data-qa_selector="js_lazy_loaded_content"></a></p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="13:1-15:0">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#installation" class="anchor" id="user-content-installation"></a>Installation</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="16:1-16:78">Since Buck is used to build Buck, the initial build process involves 2 phases:</p>
<h5 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="18:1-18:61">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#1-clone-the-buck-repository-and-bootstrap-it-with-ant" class="anchor" id="user-content-1-clone-the-buck-repository-and-bootstrap-it-with-ant"></a>1. Clone the Buck repository and bootstrap it with ant:</h5>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-plaintext white" lang="plaintext" data-sourcepos="20:5-23:0" id="code-2"><code><span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC1">git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/facebook/buck.git</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC2">cd buck</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC3">ant</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-2"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="24:1-24:165">You must be using Java 8 or 11 for this to compile successfully. If you see compilation errors from ant, check your <code>JAVA_HOME</code> is pointing at one of these versions.</p>
<h5 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="26:1-26:56">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#2-use-bootstrapped-version-of-buck-to-build-buck" class="anchor" id="user-content-2-use-bootstrapped-version-of-buck-to-build-buck"></a>2. Use bootstrapped version of Buck to build Buck:</h5>
<div class="gl-relative markdown-code-block js-markdown-code">
<pre data-canonical-lang="" class="code highlight js-syntax-highlight language-plaintext white" lang="plaintext" data-sourcepos="28:5-32:0" id="code-3"><code><span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC1">./bin/buck build --show-output buck</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC2"># output will contain something like</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC3"># //programs:buck buck-out/gen/programs/buck.pex</span>
<span lang="plaintext" class="line" id="LC4">buck-out/gen/programs/buck.pex --help</span></code></pre>
<copy-code><button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-md gl-button btn-icon has-tooltip" data-title="Copy to clipboard" data-clipboard-target="pre#code-3"><svg><use xlink:href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#copy-to-clipboard"></use></svg></button></copy-code>
</div>
<h5 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="33:1-33:28">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#prebuilt-buck-binaries" class="anchor" id="user-content-prebuilt-buck-binaries"></a>Prebuilt buck binaries</h5>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="35:1-35:550">Pre-built binaries of buck for any buck <code>sha</code> can be downloaded from <code>https://jitpack.io/com/github/facebook/buck/<sha>/buck-<sha>.pex</code>. The very first time a version of buck is requested, it is built via <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://jitpack.io/" target="_blank">jitpack</a>. As a result, it could take a few minutes for this initial binary to become available. Every subsequent request will just serve the built artifact directly. This functionality is available for any fork of buck as well, so you can fetch <code>https://jitpack.io/com/github/<github-user-or-org>/buck/<sha>/buck-<sha>.pex</code></p>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="37:1-37:85">For buck binaries built for JDK 11, modify end of the url to <code>buck-<sha>-java11.pex</code>.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="39:1-41:0">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#feature-deprecation" class="anchor" id="user-content-feature-deprecation"></a>Feature Deprecation</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="42:1-42:349">Buck tries to move fast with respect to its internals. However, for user facing features (build rules, command line interface, etc), the Buck team tries to have a graceful deprecation process. Note that this generally applies only to documented functionality, or functionality that is less documented, but appears to be in wide use. That process is:</p>
<ul dir="auto" data-sourcepos="44:1-49:0">
<li data-sourcepos="44:1-45:194">An issue is opened on Github suggesting what will be deprecated, and when it will be removed. For larger features that are deprecated, there may be a period when the default is the new setting, and the old behavior may only be used with a configuration change.
<ul data-sourcepos="45:3-45:194">
<li data-sourcepos="45:3-45:194">
<a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://github.com/facebook/buck/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aopen+label%3Aannouncement+label%3Adeprecation" target="_blank">In-progress deprecation issues</a> are tagged with 'announcement' and 'deprecation'</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-sourcepos="46:1-46:213">A change is submitted to Buck that puts the old behavior behind a configuration flag and sets the default to the old behavior. These flags can be found at <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="https://buck.build/concept/buckconfig.html#incompatible" target="_blank">https://buck.build/concept/buckconfig.html#incompatible</a>.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="47:1-47:158">For larger features, a change eventually is put in place that sets the default to the new behavior. e.g. when Skylark becomes the default build file parser.</li>
<li data-sourcepos="48:1-49:0">When the removal date is reached, a change is submitted to remove the feature. At this point, the configuration value will still parse, but will not be used by Buck internally.</li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="50:1-52:18">
<a aria-hidden="true" href="#license" class="anchor" id="user-content-license"></a>License</h2>
<p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="52:1-52:18">Apache License 2.0</p>
</div>

</div>
</div></div></article></div>

    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now
    if (imgUrl.indexOf('/avatar/') > -1 && imgUrl.indexOf('?') === -1) {
      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

//]]>
</script>
